# Time Complexity:- O(n)
# Space Complexity:- O(n)
class Solution:
    def removeDuplicates(self, arr):
        idx = 0
        n = len(arr)
        result = [arr[0]]
        
        for i in range(1, n):
            number = arr[i]
            if number != result[-1]:
                result.append(arr[i])
                
        return result
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Approach Explanation

Keep a result array to store unique elements.

Always compare current element arr[i] with the last added element (result[-1]).

If different â†’ append it.

At the end, result contains only unique elements.
